creator: michael@fiftypercentgray.com
text:
Here is the last line that make outputs, along with the errors. I am using 
libtool 1.5.6, m4 1.4.1, and autoconf 2.59. This started happening after I 
copied mod_mya into the Apache 2.0.49 source modules directory and ran 
buildconf in the Apache 2.0 source directory.

Found newer headers. Will rebuild exports.c.
rm -f exports.c export_files
tmp=export_files_unsorted.txt;  rm -f $tmp && touch $tmp;  for dir 
in /usr/local/httpd-2.0.49/include /usr/local/httpd-
2.0.49/os/unix /usr/local/httpd-2.0.49/srclib/apr/include /usr/local/httpd-
2.0.49/srclib/apr-util/include /usr/local/httpd-2.0.49/modules/http; do  ls 
$dir/*.h >> $tmp;  done;  sort -u $tmp > export_files;  rm -f $tmp
nawk -f /usr/local/httpd-2.0.49/build/make_exports.awk `cat export_files` > 
exports.c
/usr/local/httpd-2.0.49/srclib/apr/libtool --silent --mode=compile gcc  -g -
